Section 1:
1 L.D. 1542
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 STATE AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 626, L.D. 1542, “An Act to Amend the
10 Membership of the Washington County Budget Advisory Committee”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §900-B by striking out all of subsection 2-A (page 1,
12 lines 42 to 44 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
13 '2-A. Member from unorganized territory. The county commissioners shall select,
14 by majority vote, one member who is a resident of the unorganized territory in Washington
15 County who has not served in or been employed by Washington County government within
16 the past 3 years and is not a current employee of Washington County government as a
17 voting member of the budget advisory committee to serve a 3-year term.'
18 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
19 number to read consecutively.
20 SUMMARY
2211 This amendment amends the bill by specifying that the county commissioners must
2222 select, by majority vote, one member who is a resident of the unorganized territory in
2233 Washington County who has not served in or been employed by Washington County
2244 government within the past 3 years and is not a current employee of Washington County
2255 government as a voting member of the budget advisory committee to serve a 3-year term.
Page 1 - 132LR1029(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
